<br>
Well, I was thinking about this whole wizard balance thing, and I started thinking of how wizards and tanks appear to be designed like cheetahs and wolves.  Cheetahs have excellent speed but have poor endurance (Wizards have the potential to deal massive damage fast but quickly use up mana).  Wolves can't run as fast but have great endurance (Tanks don't deal as much damage at once, but can keep hitting as long as hp allow, which is a long time with clerics healing them).<br>
<br>
Unfortunately the Wizards at high levels are like cheetahs taken into the future with no chance to evolve.  Suddenly the wolves can run as fast or almost as fast as the cheetahs (better equipment) and yet they still have great endurance (healers and buffers haven't gotten any weaker which is good!).  To make matters worse, the prey (mobs) have also evolved so that they can run faster (high MR and AC) for longer periods of time (high HP).  What's a cheetah to do?<br>
<br>
Akailen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uammeroutcaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ammer Outcaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/01 6:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Of cheetahs and wolves...</span><hr size=1> Well, I see most of you have some nice ideas. But, yet again Verant wont fix it. I've had enough with their bs on balancing and what not and I'm sick of waiting. So... you can count me out of EverQuest forever, as for Verant's responses to our class don't thrill me at all. If that's what they think so be it, I'll just leave. Well, later all.<br>
