<br>
Cleric complains &quot;my aggro is too high, if I heal I get the mob on me and druids can heal now so all I'm needed for is rezzes and all verant does is nerf me&quot; (fault, they get a rez stick for an epic (relatively easy to get too as well as healing BP's (recently nerfed) and Heal over time, invaluable to any xp or raiding group)<br>
<br>
Magician &quot;I get no root, my nukes don't hit alot of the time and my pet is weak for the mobs I want to fight (problem being, pets constantly deal melee dmg in a group even when they're OOM, they do still have comprabable nukes even though they do have a high resist rate (we get resisted our fair share too) but they do also get major debuffs as well as dmg shields for tanks.<br>
<br>
Rogue &quot;My AC is too low and my aggro is too high&quot; (yes this is what he said basically)(problem being that's their deal, high dmg for low defense and lower selection of weapons and armor, that was in their class description and they do get disciplines)<br>
<br>
Warrior (yes even he had complaints) HP's are not adequate for high lvl mobs, not strong individually and very dependant on spell casting classes. (duh I don't think tanks have any cause to complain, geez they were freakin handed cobalt armor which gives them spells and they get melee disciplines, they knew all that when they got the job, plus we all know invaluable as meat shields and taunt machines for mobs)<br>
<br>
Monk - He actually didn't have any complaints though I'm sure many monks have some.<br>
<br>
Wizards - Nowhere does it say that a wizard will a) be totally useless when out of mana b) is highly resisted even with his lure lines c) have excessive aggro even when outdamaged by a taunting tank d) Be unappreciated by groups and never improved by Verant.  What has me the most pissed off is instead of increasing our mana pool, mana regen, fizzle rate or resist rate, all which are directly related to mana and our effectiveness, they put in 2 lvl 60 QUESTING spells (if you don't have a high lvl group to kill these mobs for you, you're not getting it) which DO have a good mana ratio I think but is a) limited to selected targets b)  Probably do fizzle too much c) Cost 20pp to cast (geez who else has to use peridot's to cast a DD?) d) remotely balance the end-game at 60 and in no way balances the levels between 35-59 where you can hunt in velious but prolly won't get loot since most caster gear (especially wizard only) is NO DROP while melee's can buy a good deal of equipment (especially the kunark class armor, hell even monks got that new crescent stuff with kunark, what did wizards get? the Dagger of frost and a epic with a self only dmg shield YAY).<br>
<br>
I'm not saying the other classes complaints aren't valid necessarily, but at least they're desired in groups, if a mage's pet dies, at least they can cast another and keep on going.  Wizards are the only class with no direct melee ability via pet or otherwise and are completely mana dependant with no other redeeming feature than dmg (except for the obvious ports and evacs but we have no abilities or skills that are UNIQUE to us as a class).  The lure line has been so nerfed that the mana/dmg ratio is obscene especially with such high resists in velious.  The only class I think that may be more screwed over than we are, are the SK's (and they've recently been awarded new spells including necro's summon corpse, new disciplines and less resistance on their HT).  They need desperate help too, but we are Verant's problem child.  Hell, at this point I'd be happy if they just handed us a major debuff like malosi, that might help solve some of our problems, but nah, why would verant give us the ability to do what we were born to?  Just change the description and they can point to it and say this is what you signed up for. <br>
<br>
Yaldin<br>
49 Wizard<br>
Karana Server<br>
Storm`s Justice<br>
<br>
&quot;Pre-Kunark and Pre-Velious we were gods, now we're taxi's, hey I don't think druids are strong enough with roots, snares, DD's, DoT's, pets and improved healing, maybe they ought to rez too?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=280.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=280.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=280.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=280.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=280.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=280.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=280.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form a